  "texts": [
    "Moreover, state constraints must also be explicitly considered during the estimation phase, an essential aspect for most data-based models (e.g., amplitudebounded hidden states in RNNs due to activation functions [20]).",
    "However, to the best of the authors' knowledge, no method has yet been proposed for constrained state estimation in ensemble models.In light of the above discussion, this paper makes two main contributions.",
    "Firstly, we propose an MPC formulation that employs an ensemble model whose experts are combined using the statistical Mahalanobis distance [21].",
    "Specifically, the proposed approach assigns combination weights according to the statistical proximity between the current operating condition and each expert's training input data.",
    "This allows the combination weights to be determined solely as a function of the input, whose future sequence is available in MPC frameworks."
  ],
